          <heading>Section 383-79</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§383-79  Combining services performed for
predecessor and successor employing units.
If any employing unit succeeds
to or acquires the organization or business of another, the number of employees
performing a service and the number of weeks during which the service is
performed for the predecessor and successor shall be combined for the purpose
of determining whether the service is subject to this chapter if the service is
agricultural labor or service described in section [383-7(a)(4)(B)(ii)]. [L
1963, c 174, §2; Supp, §93-78; am L 1967, c 51, §2; HRS §383-79]
